post_text:
Beginning of School
Staggered Starts

Students in Grades 1-12 will start school on a staggered start plan.

Students with a last name beginning A-J will attend on Wednesday, September 9.

Students with a last name beginning K-Z will attend on Thursday, September 10.

All 1-12 grade students will attend on Friday, September 11.

Kindergarten students will start school a week later, using a staggered start plan.

Students with a last name beginning A-J will attend on Monday, September 14.

Students with a last name beginning K-Z will attend on Tuesday, September 15.

All kindergarten students will attend on Wednesday, September 16.

post_text:
The National School Lunch Program is temporarily offering students free meals (breakfast and lunch). According to the USDA, students will have free meals until December 31, 2020, or until funding runs out to help children have nutritious food as the country recovers from the COVID-19 pandemic.

Beginning on our first day of school, all students K-12 may receive a free tray. Students are encouraged to still have money on their PaySchools account for additional purchases such as snacks, extra entrees, extra milk, etc.

Free and Reduced School Meal Applications are available on our website (PayForIt.net, located under Parent Tab, Cafeteria & Fee On Line Payment) for the 2020-2021 school year. We encourage all eligible families to fill out the application in order to be ready to resume the Free and Reduced School Lunch program and for other qualifying purposes.

West Branch Board of Education is currently accepting applications to fill the unexpired term of School Board Member John Wallace. If interested, please complete and return the application along with a one page summary explaining why you want to serve on the board to Treasurer Julia Rozsnyai by no later than 3:00 p.m. on September 4th.

Applicants must be a registered voter and district resident. The newly appointed school board member will serve until December 31, 2021 and will have to seek election to continue in the post.

post_text:
IMMUNIZATION REQUIREMENTS FOR 7TH AND 12TH GRADE ENTRY

The Ohio Department of Health requires all students prior to entering 7th and 12th grades receive immunization updates. The required immunizations are as follows:

7th Grade: Tetanus, Diphtheria, and Pertussis (Tdap) booster and a Meningitis (MCV4) vaccine

12th Grade: A second dose of Meningitis (MCV4) vaccine or may be the first dose if it’s given after the age of 16.

Documentation of having received these vaccines must be provided to the school or provide a medical, religious, or philosophical exemption form. (Ohio Revised Code 3701.13)

Teaching STEM during these remote learning times is challenging since it is a project-based curriculum, but the students did an exceptional job with this project.

Students in 7/8th grade STEM at West Branch Middle School competed a Theme Park Ride Attraction for Walt Disney World. UPDATE on Food Service Operations - A few changes...

We want to limit travel outside of the home, and follow our Governor’s direction on stopping the spread of COVID-19.

We are updating and changing our delivery plan beginning this Friday March 27th.

Meals will be available Tuesdays and Fridays - beginning this Friday 3/27/2020 - going forward...

When: 11 a.m. - 12:30 p.m.(NEW TIME)

Who: Anyone - 18 years or younger(Students do not have to qualify for Free/Reduced meals)

What: Grab-n-Go Lunch & Breakfast(s) for multiple days.

Where: There are 5(five) pick-up locations:

West Branch High School
Damascus Elementary
Homeworth FD Parking Lots
Goshen PD
North Benton United Presbyterian Church

Please only go to one location.

Questions can be directed to the Superintendent's office at 330-938-9324.

post_text:
UPDATE -

The regular board of education meeting will be held on Thursday March 19, 2020 in the West Branch High School Media Center.

Time: 6:00 p.m.

Note:

In light of Ohio Governor Mike DeWine’s order limiting mass gatherings, similar guidance from the Centers for Disease Control, as well as the written guidance received from Ohio Attorney General Dave Yost, the Board will move forward with its scheduled meeting on March 19, 2020 at West Branch High School(Media Center).

In compliance with Ohio’s Open Meetings Act, the meeting remains open to the public, however, the District will livestream the meeting via Facebook utilizing the districts page(https://www.facebook.com/WBLSD/) and physical attendance by non-invited personnel will not be permitted.

The District recognizes the importance of public comment and therefore, anyone who wishes to comment publicly can email a statement within the same limitations as a regular board meeting to any Board Member or the Superintendent and the statement will be read aloud at the board meeting.
text:
UPDATE -

The regular board of education meeting will be held on Thursday March 19, 2020 in the West Branch High School Media Center.

Time: 6:00 p.m.

Note:

In light of Ohio Governor Mike DeWine’s order limiting mass gatherings, similar guidance from the Centers for Disease Control, as well as the written guidance received from Ohio Attorney General Dave Yost, the Board will move forward with its scheduled meeting on March 19, 2020 at West Branch High School(Media Center).

In compliance with Ohio’s Open Meetings Act, the meeting remains open to the public, however, the District will livestream the meeting via Facebook utilizing the districts page(https://www.facebook.com/WBLSD/) and physical attendance by non-invited personnel will not be permitted.

The District recognizes the importance of public comment and therefore, anyone who wishes to comment publicly can email a statement within the same limitations as a regular board meeting to any Board Member or the Superintendent and the statement will be read aloud at the board meeting.

Greetings Warrior Nation - Out of an abundance of caution, the West Branch Local School District will be scheduling a Waiver Day this Friday, March 13th. There will be no classes for students.

Classes will resume as scheduled Monday, March 16th if allowable.

As the presence of the COVID-19 Virus looms in Ohio, staff members will report to work this Friday and prepare for alternative instructional protocols should the need arise.

The District continues to monitor the latest guidance from the Centers for Disease Control and the Ohio Department of Health. Our teachers will proactively spend the upcoming weekend to prepare. We would ask your families to begin to plan for arrangements should the District be forced to interrupt normal operations. Thank you, Timothy Saxton, Superintendent.

(Fifth - Eighth Grade Girls)

Tuesdays & Thursdays
March 3 -- May 16, 2020
After School Until 4:15

Girls on the Run (GOTR) is a North American non-profit program that works
to encourage pre-teen girls to develop self-respect and healthy
lifestyles through dynamic, interactive lessons and running games,
culminating in a celebratory 5k run. The organization's curricula seek
to address all aspects of the girls' development to enhance their physical,
emotional, mental and social well-being while establishing a lifetime
appreciation of health and fitness.

post_text:
Back Pack Food Program

The West Branch staff is teaming up with local churches, community organizations and the community to provide food to students on weekends.

If you would like to donate (even just one item), please feel free to drop your donation off to any school office and we will put it on our shelves for distribution. These donations will be accepted throughout the school year.

Here are a few suggestions:

Boxes of Cereal, Cereal Bars, Pop Tarts
Peanut Butter and Jelly (plastic jars please), Crackers with cheese
Snacks - pudding cups, fruit cups, granola bars
Canned food - meats, pastas, soups, veggies
Monetary donations to purchase bread products
Any other non-perishable items that could be used for breakfast or lunches

Thanks for your continued support.
